 {"id":"bd-1nnm","title":"Fix unbounded conversation history in ACP/Claude SDK drivers","description":"# Bug: Unbounded Conversation History Causes Memory Leak

## Problem Statement
Both the ACP driver and Claude SDK driver push messages to `session.conversationHistory` without any size limit. In long-running agent sessions, this array grows indefinitely, eventually exhausting memory.

## Affected Files
1. `packages/agent-drivers/src/acp/acp-driver.ts` (lines 290-294)
2. `packages/agent-drivers/src/sdk/claude-driver.ts` (lines 152-157, 404-413)

## Current Behavior (BROKEN)
```typescript
// ACP driver - line 290
session.conversationHistory.push({
  role: "user",
  content: [{ type: "text", text: message }],
  timestamp: new Date(),
});
// Array grows forever
```

## Impact
- **Memory exhaustion**: Long-running agents (hours/days) will OOM
- **Performance degradation**: Large arrays slow down serialization and API calls
- **Context overflow**: Sending entire history to API exceeds context limits

## Root Cause
No maximum size enforcement on conversation history arrays. Messages are added but never removed or summarized.

## Proposed Solution
Implement a sliding window with configurable max size:

### Option A: Simple FIFO Truncation
```typescript
const MAX_HISTORY_MESSAGES = 100;

session.conversationHistory.push(message);
if (session.conversationHistory.length > MAX_HISTORY_MESSAGES) {
  // Keep system message (index 0) + recent messages
  const systemMsg = session.conversationHistory[0];
  session.conversationHistory = [
    systemMsg,
    ...session.conversationHistory.slice(-MAX_HISTORY_MESSAGES + 1)
  ];
}
```

### Option B: Token-Based Truncation (Better)
```typescript
const MAX_HISTORY_TOKENS = 50000;  // Configurable based on model context

session.conversationHistory.push(message);
let totalTokens = session.conversationHistory.reduce(
  (sum, msg) => sum + countTokens(msg.content), 0
);

while (totalTokens > MAX_HISTORY_TOKENS && session.conversationHistory.length > 2) {
  // Remove oldest non-system message
  const removed = session.conversationHistory.splice(1, 1)[0];
  totalTokens -= countTokens(removed.content);
}
```

### Option C: Summarization (Advanced)
When history exceeds threshold, summarize older messages into a single "context" message. This preserves information while reducing token count. (May be overkill for initial fix.)

## Implementation Details

### Configuration
Add to driver config:
```typescript
interface DriverConfig {
  maxHistoryMessages?: number;  // Default: 100
  maxHistoryTokens?: number;    // Default: 50000
  historyStrategy?: "fifo" | "token-based" | "summarize";
}
```

### Shared Utility
Create a helper function in base-driver.ts:
```typescript
protected pruneConversationHistory(
  history: ConversationMessage[],
  config: HistoryConfig
): ConversationMessage[] {
  // Implementation
}
```

## Testing Requirements

### Unit Tests
1. Test that history is capped at configured max
2. Test that system message is preserved during pruning
3. Test token-based pruning calculates correctly
4. Test edge cases: empty history, single message, exactly at limit

### Memory Tests
1. Create agent, send 1000 messages, verify memory stable
2. Compare memory usage before/after pruning
3. Verify no memory leak over extended operation

### Integration Tests
1. Verify agent still functions correctly after history pruning
2. Verify conversation coherence is maintained
3. Test that API calls don't exceed context limits

## Considerations
- **System message preservation**: The first message is often a system prompt; must not be pruned
- **Conversation coherence**: Aggressive pruning may break multi-turn conversations
- **Token counting accuracy**: Use same tokenizer as target model for accurate limits
- **Backward compatibility**: Default behavior should be current (no limit) with opt-in pruning

## Definition of Done
- [ ] HistoryConfig added to driver configuration
- [ ] pruneConversationHistory helper implemented
- [ ] ACP driver updated to prune history
- [ ] Claude SDK driver updated to prune history
- [ ] Unit tests for all pruning strategies
- [ ] Memory profiling shows stable usage
- [ ] Integration tests pass
